You find yourself standing on the bridge outside of Hogwarts with Ron and Hermione holding the Elder wand in your hand. Hermione asks, “Why didn’t it work for him, the Elder Wand”. You respond to him and tell her “It answered to somebody else. When he killed Snape, he thought the wand would become his, but the thing is, the wand never belong to Snape. It was Draco who disarmed Dumbledore that night in the astrology tower. From that moment on, the wand answered to him. Until... the other night when I disarmed Draco at Malfloy manor, which means, the wand responded to me.” Ron asks, “Well what will you do with it?” You turn to the edge of the bridge, break it in half, and throw it over. 